.TH "cpuset_hotplug_update_tasks" 9 "cpuset_hotplug_update_tasks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpuset_hotplug_update_tasks \- update tasks in a cpuset for hotunplug
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cpuset_hotplug_update_tasks
.BI "(struct cpuset *cs "  ","
.BI "struct tmpmasks *tmp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cs" 12
cpuset in interest
.IP "tmp" 12
the tmpmasks structure pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Compare \fIcs\fP's cpu and mem masks against top_cpuset and if some have gone
offline, update \fIcs\fP accordingly.  If \fIcs\fP ends up with no CPU or memory,
all its tasks are moved to the nearest ancestor with both resources.
